            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. Whisk the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{caster-sugar}} in a bowl. Rub in the {{unsalted-butter}} until the mix looks like coarse breadcrumbs. Whisk the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "sourdough discard",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99d5r400003gv46ds2kfku"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " into the {{whole-milk}} until smooth.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring together and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the {{sourdough-starter}}-and-milk mixture into the flour. Stir with a palette knife in figure-of-eight strokes until the dough comes together. It will feel a touch wetter than a plain scone dough. Tip onto a floured surface and pat to a 3 cm slab. Cut twelve rounds with a 5 cm cutter pressed straight down.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set on a lined tray. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes; the tops should be deep gold and the sides should look risen and dry. Cool on a rack 5 minutes before splitting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
